# Model vs Entity Separation

## Core principle
- **Domain class** → `domain/entity/`, plain Dart, **no JSON**, no `Entity` suffix — default **`Equatable`** (or enums)
- **Freezed on entities** → only when justified (see below); **must** use `domain/entity/<entity_snake_name>/` with the main file + `part '*.freezed.dart'` inside that folder — never a lone `@freezed` file directly under `entity/`
- **Model** → `data/models/<model_name>/`, extends domain class, `@JsonSerializable`, no Freezed

The domain never knows how data is serialized.
The model extends the domain class — a `RouteModel` IS a `Route`.

## File locations and naming

```
lib/src/features/routes/
  domain/
    entity/
      routes_route.dart          ← class Route extends Equatable
      routes_route_type.dart     ← class RouteType extends Equatable
  data/
    models/
      routes_route_model/
        routes_route_model.dart  ← @JsonSerializable class RouteModel extends Route
```

```
lib/src/features/user_config/
  domain/
    entity/
      app_theme_mode.dart        ← enum AppThemeMode (distinct type name; feature folder scopes it)
```

```
lib/src/features/<feature>/
  domain/
    entity/
      example_todo/
        example_todo.dart        ← @freezed class ExampleTodo with _$ExampleTodo; part 'example_todo.freezed.dart';
        example_todo.freezed.dart
```

- **Equatable entity** (default): single file — prefer `<feature_name>_<name>.dart` when the concept name could collide across features; otherwise a distinctive name such as `app_theme_mode.dart`.
- **Freezed entity** (exception): folder `entity/<entity_snake_name>/` where `<entity_snake_name>` matches the primary Dart basename (e.g. `ExampleTodo` → `example_todo/` and `example_todo.dart`). Keep generated `*.freezed.dart` next to the main file in that folder.
- Class `<Name>` (no `Entity` suffix)
- Model folder: `data/models/<feature_name>_<name>_model/`
- Model file: `data/models/<feature_name>_<name>_model/<feature_name>_<name>_model.dart` — class `<Name>Model`

## When to use Freezed on an entity
Prefer **`Equatable`** for ordinary immutable data classes. Use **`@freezed`** only when there is a concrete benefit, for example:
- A **union** of variants where **`copyWith`**, canonical **equality**, and **pattern matching** (`switch` / `case`) are enough
- **Many** fields where generated `copyWith` / equality reduces noise and mistakes

If none of that applies, use `Equatable`. **Do not** put `@freezed` on `data/models` classes — models stay `json_serializable` only.

## Freezed must match `build.yaml` (no JSON, no `map` / `when`)
The project root **`build.yaml`** configures the Freezed builder with:

- `from_json: false`
- `to_json: false`
- `when: false`
- `map: false`

Therefore:

- ❌ Never add **`fromJson` / `toJson`**, **`@JsonSerializable`**, or **`json_annotation`** on domain Freezed entities — wire JSON only in **`data/models`** via `RouteModel`-style classes.
- ❌ Never call **`.map`** or **`.when`** on Freezed domain types — those members are **not generated**. Use Dart **`switch`** (including exhaustiveness on sealed variants), **`if` / `is`**, or small hand-written helpers instead.
- Keep **`build.yaml`** as the single source of truth for these flags — do not re-enable Freezed JSON or `map`/`when` generation to push serialization into domain or BLoC types.

BLoC event/state Freezed types use the same `build.yaml` settings: no Freezed **`fromJson`/`toJson`**, and no **`.map`/`.when`** — use **`switch`** on concrete event/state subclasses, `copyWith`, and equality helpers instead.

## Domain class — default: Equatable, no JSON

```dart
// ✅ GOOD — lib/src/features/routes/domain/entity/routes_route.dart
import 'package:equatable/equatable.dart';

class Route extends Equatable {
  final String id;
  final String title;
  final String description;
  final double distanceKm;
  final int durationMinutes;
  final RouteType type;

  const Route({
    required this.id,
    required this.title,
    required this.description,
    required this.distanceKm,
    required this.durationMinutes,
    required this.type,
  });

  @override
  List<Object?> get props => [id, title, description, distanceKm, durationMinutes, type];
}

// ❌ BAD
class RouteEntity extends Equatable { ... }  // Entity suffix
class Route {                                 // No Equatable — equality broken
  @override bool operator ==(Object other) => ...  // manual equality, skip Equatable

// ❌ BAD — Freezed at entity root without a subfolder
// lib/.../domain/entity/routes_route.dart:
// @freezed abstract class Route with _$Route { ... }

// ✅ GOOD — Freezed only under entity/<snake_name>/
// lib/.../domain/entity/example_todo/example_todo.dart
import 'package:freezed_annotation/freezed_annotation.dart';

part 'example_todo.freezed.dart';

@freezed
class ExampleTodo with _$ExampleTodo {
  const factory ExampleTodo({
    required String id,
    required String title,
    @Default(false) bool done,
  }) = _ExampleTodo;
}
```

## Data Model — extends domain class, json_serializable, no Freezed

Model extends the entity, so `RouteModel` satisfies `Route` everywhere — no `toEntity()` needed.
`fromEntity()` IS required as a named constructor for write-back scenarios (POST/PUT to API).

```dart
// ✅ GOOD — lib/src/features/routes/data/models/routes_route_model/routes_route_model.dart
import 'package:json_annotation/json_annotation.dart';
import 'package:mobile_app/src/features/routes/domain/entity/routes_route.dart';

part 'routes_route_model.g.dart';

@JsonSerializable()
class RouteModel extends Route {
  const RouteModel({
    required super.id,
    required super.title,
    required super.description,
    @JsonKey(name: 'distance_km') required super.distanceKm,
    @JsonKey(name: 'duration_minutes') required super.durationMinutes,
    required super.type,
  });

  // ── Deserialization ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  factory RouteModel.fromJson(Map<String, dynamic> json) =>
      _$RouteModelFromJson(json);

  Map<String, dynamic> toJson() => _$RouteModelToJson(this);

  // ── Entity conversion ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  /// Creates a model from a domain object (used when writing back to API).
  factory RouteModel.fromEntity(Route route) => RouteModel(
        id: route.id,
        title: route.title,
        description: route.description,
        distanceKm: route.distanceKm,
        durationMinutes: route.durationMinutes,
        type: route.type,
      );
}

// ❌ BAD
@freezed abstract class RouteModel with _$RouteModel { ... }  // No Freezed on models
class RouteModel {                                             // Doesn't extend domain class
  final String id;
  RouteModel.fromEntity(Route r) { ... }                      // fromEntity outside class body
```

## Repository: no .toEntity() needed
Since `RouteModel extends Route`, the repository returns `RouteModel` typed as `Route` — no conversion method needed.
Use `RouteModel.fromEntity(route)` when serializing a domain object for a write (POST/PUT) request.

## Strict rules summary

| Rule | Domain class | Model |
|------|-------------|-------|
| Location | `domain/entity/` (Freezed: `domain/entity/<snake_name>/`) | `data/models/<feature_name>_<name>_model/` |
| Class suffix | ❌ None (no `Entity`) | ✅ `Model` |
| Extends | `Equatable` (default) or `@freezed` in subfolder only | Domain class (e.g. `Route`) |
| Freezed | ✅ Only when needed; only inside `entity/<snake_name>/` with `part '*.freezed.dart'` | ❌ Never |
| `Equatable` + `props` | ✅ Default for non-enum data classes; skip if using `@freezed` in subfolder | inherited from domain class |
| `fromJson` / `toJson` | ❌ Never (including Freezed + JSON — disabled in `build.yaml`) | ✅ Always (model only) |
| Freezed `.map` / `.when` | ❌ Not generated (`build.yaml`) — do not use | — |
| `@JsonKey` | ❌ Never | ✅ Allowed |
| `fromEntity()` constructor | ❌ Never | ✅ Named constructor inside model |
| `toEntity()` method | not needed — model IS domain class | — |
| Imported by BLoC / UseCase | ✅ Domain class only | ❌ Never |
